President Biden and President López Obrador of Mexico held a meeting at the Moscone Convention Center in San Francisco. They discussed their cooperation in various areas, including security, economics, and migration. President Biden praised Mexico for its efforts in combating arms trafficking, organized crime, and the opioid epidemic. He also mentioned his conversation with Chinese President Xi Jinping about the issue of fentanyl. Both leaders emphasized the importance of a balanced approach to migration, which includes enforcing borders, increasing reparations, and opening legal pathways for migrants. President López Obrador expressed his satisfaction with the relationship between the two countries and thanked President Biden for opening legal pathways for migration. He also commended President Biden for not building walls and expressed Mexico's commitment to preventing the entry of fentanyl and other drugs into the United States. The two leaders highlighted the friendship and cooperation between their countries and welcomed Mexican migrants living in the United States.